Reasoning: The paper deals with the optimization of degrees-of-freedom in a multi-user communication system, specifically the MISO Broadcast Channel, in the presence of delayed and imperfect channel-state information. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM). The paper also discusses the use of a hierarchical quantizer, which could potentially fall under the sub-categories of signal processing (cs.SI) or networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the paper proposes a novel scheme that deviates from existing efforts, which could be of interest to researchers in machine learning (cs.LG).
